               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0117GBI">Gʷaḥgot ʾIyasus / GBI</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1700" notAfter="1730">King Bäkaffa (r. 1721-30) is
                        mentioned throughout the Ms. However his name is always written over
                        erasures (<locus target="#7vc">7vc</locus>, 8ra, 8vc, 9ra, 9vabc, 10ra);
                        therefore the Ms. might antedate his rule.</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>According to Additio 3 the Ms. was donated by
                     King Yoḥannǝs IV (r. 1872-89). His name is written over the name of King
                     Bäkaffa in the supplication formulas, e.g., 5rac,
                     5va, 6rc, 7rbc. According to Additio 3 the Ms. was donated to
                     a church dedicated to ʾAmanuʾel.
 A short note (5r, upper margin, s. "Varia") refers to the former owner, the
                     church Madḫāne ʿĀlam, which is the church at Mäqdäla founded by Tewodros II (r.
                     1855-68).</provenance></history>
